metadata.name: Lilith
metadata.description:
Known as Adam's first wife, which was born from the same soil as him, she refuses to be subservient to her husband. 

The very first she-demon, mother of the midnight, becoming the symbol of feminism and rebellion to againts patriarchy. 

In the Renaissance, Michelangelo portrayed Lilith as a half-woman, half-serpent, coiled around the Tree of Knowledge.

"And the fleets met the islands, and a goat on the other side called it; But there the night calmed down, and she found rest."

First artwork for 'Demons' series.
